// PRECISION GAP #1 (2026-04-19 audit)
// CLAIM: VRP doesn't propagate `u32 i = literal_value` through to
//        the array index. Direct `arr[10]` on size-4 array errors
//        at compile time; `u32 i = 10; arr[i]` only warns + adds
//        auto-guard.
// SAFETY: auto-guard inserts `if (i >= 4) { return 0; }` — program
//         is safe at runtime. Just a precision/message difference.
// FIX APPROACH: extend `derive_expr_range` to resolve NODE_IDENT
//               to its init expr's range when the variable was
//               assigned only once from a constant. VRP enhancement.

u32 main() {
    u32[4] arr;
    u32 i = 10;             // range [10, 10] not propagated
    return arr[i];          // warning, auto-guard, returns 0
}
